1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Italian Game } 3... Nf6 { Two Knights Defense } 4.
d3 { Modern Bishop's Opening, Defending  e4  . } 4... d5
{ Challenging the Bishop on  c4  . } 5. exd5
{ Exchanging a pair of center pawns. } 5... Nxd5 6. O-O
{ Preparing to put a Rook on the semi-open e-file. } 6... Bg4
{ Pinning the Knight on  f3  to the Queen. } 7. Re1 { Controlling the e-file. }
7... f6
{ Black thinks the pawn on  f6  is protecting the  e5  pawn... But this is a blunder. }
8. Nxe5
{ Only a few players found this move! Allowing Black to capture White's Queen. But the e-file is now open for the Rook to give a nasty discovered check. }
8... Bxd1 { There are no good move at this point. } 9. Nxc6+
{ Capturing the Knight on  c6  with a discovered attack on the King, while attacking Black's Queen @@StartBracket@@+6.5@@EndBracket@@. }
