1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Italian Game } 3... Nf6 { Two Knights Defense } 4.
d4 { Open Variation, An agressive move. } 4... Be7
{ A blunder. Black has forgotten that his center pawn is attacked more than he is defending it. }
5. dxe5
{ Capturing with the pawn is White's best move, chasing the  f6  Knight.   After  5.Nxe5  O-O  , Black is doing relatively well. }
5... Ng4 6. Qd5 { Centralizing the Queen, threatening checkmate on  f7  . }
6... O-O { Preventing from getting checkmated. } 7. h3
{ Forcing the Knight to flee to the unpromising  h6  square. White is a pawn up, controls the center and has the initiative @@StartBracket@@+3.0@@EndBracket@@. }
