1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Italian Game } 3... Nf6 { Two Knights Defense } 4.
d4 { Open Variation, An agressive move. } 4... d6
{ Scotch Gambit Declined, Defending the pawn on  e5  . } 5. dxe5
{ Trading a pair of center pawns. } 5... dxe5 6. Qxd8+ { Trading Queens. } 6...
Kxd8
{ An inaccuracy.   6...Nxd8  is the correct move. After  7.Nxe5  Nxe4  , the game is about equal. The Knight on  d8  is protecting  f7  . }
7. Bxf7 { The best way to punish Black's mistake. } 7... Nxe4 8. Bd5
{ Another key move! Forking both Knights. } 8... Bf5
{ Defending the undefended Knight. } 9. Bxc6
{ Capturing the defender of the  e5  pawn. } 9... bxc6 10. Nxe5
{ Winning a pawn, and another one will fall soon. Black is left with a shattered pawn structure @@StartBracket@@+1.5@@EndBracket@@. }
