[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Italian Game } 3... Nf6 { Two Knights Defense } 4.
Ng5 { Knight Attack } 4... Bc5
{ Traxler Counterattack or Wilkes-Barre Variation } 5. Nxf7
{ Knight Sacrifice Line } 5... Qe7
{ This move is too passive. The point of 4... Bc5 was to launch a counterattack, not to respond to White's attacking moves! }
6. Nxh8 Nxe4
{ This poor move was played hundreds of times... Grabbing back a single pawn isn't enough for Black to make a chance to win the game. }
7. Qh5+ g6 8. Nxg6
{ If  8...hxg6  , then  9.Qxg6+  will win back the Knight on  e4  next move }
8... Bxf2+ { Black finally starts attacking, but now it's too late... } 9. Kd1
{ The King is safe on any square, because Black now has a serious problem: His Queen is under attack, and White is threatening a discovered attack with the Knight. White has a big advantage and should be close to winning the game @@StartBracket@@+8.0@@EndBracket@@. }
