[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Italian Game } 3... Nf6 { Two Knights Defense } 4.
Ng5 { Knight Attack } 4... Bc5
{ Traxler Counterattack or Wilkes-Barre Variation } 5. Nxf7
{ Knight Sacrifice Line } 5... Bxf2+
{ Attacking chess is the best defense in this variation! } 6. Kf1
{ The main continuation for White, and the safest one. } 6... Qe7 7. Nxh8 Nxe4
{ Defending the Bishop on  f2  . This blunder was played thousands of times! }
8. Qh5+ { Activating the Queen with a check. } 8... g6 9. Nxg6
{ Sacrificing the Knight for two pawns. } 9... hxg6 10. Qxg6+ Kd8 11. d3
{ 11.Qxe4  isn't bad, but  11.d3  will take the game to an end quicker. White is opening the diagonal for the Bishop on  c1  . If Black moves his Knight,  Bg5  would be decisive }
11... Qf8 { Putting the Queen on the same file as White's King. } 12. dxe4
{ There is no problem to capture the Knight if you know White's next moves. }
12... Be3+ 13. Ke2 { Make sure the Bishop is protected by the Rook... } 13...
Qf2+ 14. Kd1
{ White's only move to win the game @@StartBracket@@+15.0@@EndBracket@@.   14.Kd3  would end in a sad loss for White, after  14...Nb4+  15.Kc3  Qxc2+  16.Kxb4  a5+  17.Ka3  Bc5+  18.b4  axb4# }
