[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2. Italian Game, Two Knights Defense"]
[Black "Knight Attack, Normal Variation, Lolli Attack"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Italian Game } 3... Nf6 { Two Knights Defense } 4.
Ng5 { Knight Attack } 4... d5 { Normal Variation } 5. exd5 Nxd5
{ Not the best move for Black. But how do you take advantage of this? } 6. d4
{ This is the Lolli Attack, probably the best choice at higher levels @@StartBracket@@>2000 FIDE@@EndBracket@@. With this move, White protects his Knight on  g5  with the Bishop on  c1  , while challenging Black's pawn in the center. }
6... exd4
{ Grabbing 'free' material, but also opening the e-file.   6...f6  is mediocre in view of  7.dxe5!  fxg5  8.Bxd5  @@StartBracket@@+1.5@@EndBracket@@. }
7. O-O
{ By far the best move for White. It is hard for Black to find a good move at this point. This position can also occur after:   @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/pppp1ppp/2n2n2/4p3/2B1P3/5N2/PPPP1PPP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 4 4@@EndFEN@@  4.d4  exd4  5.Ng5  d5  6.exd5  Nxd5  7.O-O  . }
7... Be7 { This natural looking move is another mistake. } 8. Nxf7
{ Another Knight sacrifice! But in a better position. } 8... Kxf7 9. Qf3+
{ The same trick again, forking King and Knight in the center. } 9... Ke6
{ Defending the Knight, right?   9...Ke8  would have been a better choice here. }
10. Re1+
{ This is the whole point of White's play @@StartBracket@@opening the center with d4, and castle fast@@EndBracket@@. The Rook now can join the party with check. }
10... Ne5 { Self-pinning the second Knight. } 11. Bf4
{ White keeps attacking and pinning Black's pieces while developing his own pieces. }
11... Bf6 { Defending the Knight on  e5  . } 12. Nc3
{ Putting even more pressure on  d5  . Ready to bring the second Rook into the game. Who cares about material at this point. Black's King is in the middle of the board. }
12... dxc3 13. Rxe5+ { A third sacrifice! } 13... Bxe5 14. Re1
{ Pinning the Bishop to the King. This position is lost for Black, despite being up a lot of material @@StartBracket@@+9.5@@EndBracket@@. }
