1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Italian Game } 3... Nf6 { Two Knights Defense } 4.
Ng5 { Knight Attack } 4... d5 { Normal Variation } 5. Bxd5
{ Renewing the threat of a Knight fork on  f7  . A mistake! But how to exploit it? }
5... Nxd5 { Trading pieces. } 6. exd5 Qxg5
{ The only move that gives Black a huge advantage.  6...Qxd5  7.O-O  isn't quite as good. }
7. dxc6 Qxg2 { Capturing a pawn while attacking the Rook on  h1  . } 8. Rf1 Bh3
{ We are not taking the pawn yet! First build up the tension with a checkmate-in-1 threat. }
9. Qe2 { Defending  f1  while counter-attacking on  e5  . } 9... Qxc6
{ Only now we take the pawn with the Queen, keeping our pawn structure intact. Moreover, White's Rook now is being attacked by our Bishop. }
10. Qxe5+
{ White fell into a trap! He did win back a pawn. But after Black's next move, his position is totally lost. }
10... Kd7
{ Sidestepping the King, threatening to play Re8 the next move among other moves @@StartBracket@@-8.5@@EndBracket@@. }
