[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { Italian Game } 3... Nf6 { Two Knights Defense } 4.
Ng5 { Knight Attack } 4... d5 { Normal Variation } 5. exd5 Nd4
{ Fritz Variation, A rather dubious variation. } 6. d6
{ A mediocre move, opening the diagonal for the Bishop on  c4  , renewing the threat of a Knight fork on  f7  .   White should refute Black's previous move with  6.c3  @@StartBracket@@+1.0@@EndBracket@@. }
6... Qxd6 { The best move. } 7. Nxf7
{ This blunder is played thousands of times!   7.d3  would have been better, defending the Bishop on  c4  @@StartBracket@@+0.5@@EndBracket@@. }
7... Qc6
{ The only good move for Black, attacking both the Bishop and the pawn on  g2  . This is why White should have defended the Bishop last move! }
8. Nxh8
{ White steps into the trap with both feet.   8.O-O  was his last chance to survive, after which  8...Qxc4  9.Nxh8  Qxc2  is the best continuation. }
8... Qxg2
{ We are not interested in material  (the Bishop)  when we can give checkmate or when we can win even more material! }
9. Rf1 Qe4+
{ 9...Bg4  is even better according to the engine, but  9...Qe4+  has the nicest finish. }
10. Be2
{ White doesn't want to lose the Queen, so he usually places the Bishop in front of the King. }
10... Nf3# { The Knight on  f3  can't be taken due to a pin. Smothered mate! }
