9. Qh5 { Defending the Knight on  e5  . } 9... Qf6
{ Counter-attacking on  f2  and  e5  . Feel free to use an engine to better understand this position.   E.g.  9...Nf6  runs into  10.Qf7+!!  Kxe5  , followed by a mate-in-8! }
10. d4
{ Blocking the diagonal for the Bishop on  b6  , while defending the Knight in the center. }
10... g6 { The best move for Black... } 11. Nxg6
{ Attacking the Rook and threatening checkmate with 12. Qd5# @@StartBracket@@+3.0@@EndBracket@@. }
