{ Trading two minor pieces for a Rook and pawn on  f7  or  f2  in a situation like this is almost never a good idea! Bishop and Knight are almost always better than Rook and pawn. And maybe even more important: White just traded off all his developed pieces, leaving Black with a huge lead in development. }
