4... Nf6 { Attacking the pawn on  e4  . } 5. d4 { Challenging Black's center. }
5... exd4 { Opening the pathway for the e-pawn. } 6. e5
{ Attacking the Knight on  f6  . } 6... Ng4
{ A very bad move, played almost 3,000 times.   6...Ng8  can be met by  7.Re1  or  7.Nxd4  @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@.   6...d5  7.Bb5  is Black's best continuation @@StartBracket@@+1.0@@EndBracket@@. }
7. h3
