4. Nxe5
{ Threatening a Knight fork on  f7  . This blunder has been played over 40,000 times! It is one of the most common opening blunders. }
4... Qg5
{ A counter-attack, attacking the Knight in the center and the pawn on  g2  . }
5. Bxf7+ { The most popular move, checking the King. } 5... Ke7
{ The engine prefers  5...Kd8  , but  5...Ke7  has the highest winrate in practice, because the King can capture the Bishop on  f7  once the Knight in the center retreats. }
6. Bxg8 { Being up in material doesn't always win you the game! } 6... Qxg2
{ Attacking the Rook. } 7. Rf1 { Bringing the Rook into safety... } 7... Qxe4+
8. Qe2 Qxe2# { ... but losing the game in only 8 moves! } *

