{ Attacking the Rook on  h1  , threatening checkmate @@StartBracket@@-10.0@@EndBracket@@.   6...Qxh5?  is a lot worse, because after  7.Bxh5  Nxc2+  8.Kd1  Nxa1  , White has center control and more active pieces. Black on the other hand only has a small material advantage since the Knight is on  a1  is most likely trapped @@StartBracket@@-1.5@@EndBracket@@. }
7. Qh4+
{ A desperate check...   7.Rf1  is the alternative. But after  7...Qxe4+  8.Kd1  Qxc2+  9.Ke1  Qxc1+  10.Qd1  , Black is totally winning @@StartBracket@@-10.5@@EndBracket@@. }
7... g5
{ Blocking the check with a pawn, attacking the Queen while threatening checkmate on  h1  . White will lose the Queen or the game next move, it's game over! }
