1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 { Scotch Game } 3... exd4 4. Bc4
{ Scotch Gambit, Sacrificing a center pawn in exchange for rapid development. }
4... d6 5. Nxd4 { Equalizing material. } 5... Nxd4
{ Trading Knights. This is a poor move, since it helps activating White's Queen. }
6. Qxd4 Qf6 { Challenging White's Queen. } 7. Qd3
{ The best square for the Queen according the engine, and also by far the move with the highest winrate for White. }
7... Be6
{ Challenging White's Bishop, but leaving the pawn on  b7  unprotected. Strangely enough this blunder is the most played move. }
8. Bxe6 { Trading Bishops. } 8... Qxe6 9. Qb5+
{ Check, forking King and pawn on  b7  . } 9... Qd7 10. Qxb7
{ Grabbing a free pawn. White is a pawn up and has a better pawn structure. He is only one move away from castling @@StartBracket@@+3.5@@EndBracket@@. }
