{ 6...Kf8  is Black's second option. White could now go for  7.Bb3  . That Bishop is White's best piece on the board @@StartBracket@@+3.0@@EndBracket@@.   After  6...Kf8  ,  7.Bxg8  isn't the best in view of  7...cxb2  8.Bxb2  Rxg8  . White's best piece has been traded for a Knight that was doing nothing @@StartBracket@@+1.5@@EndBracket@@. }
7. Qd5+ { Forking King and Bishop. } 7... Ke8
{ By far the most popular move.   7...Kf8  could be followed by  8.Qxc5+  Nge7  9.Nxc3  @@StartBracket@@+2.5@@EndBracket@@. }
8. Qh5+
{ This move has a slightly higher winning chance than the direct  8.Qxc5  . Stockfish13 likes this move as well. }
8... g6
{ 8...Ke7  or  8...Kf8  would have been a bit better @@StartBracket@@+1.0@@EndBracket@@. }
9. Qxc5
{ Gaining back some material. White is still a pawn down, but he is ahead in development and controls the center. Black's King lost his castling rights @@StartBracket@@+2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
