5. e5 { Advance Variation, Chasing away the Knight on  f6  . } 5... d5
{ The best move: a counter-attack! } 6. Bb5
{ Attacking the Knight on  c6  while pinning it to the King. Other moves are less good for White. }
6... Ne4 { Saving and centralizing the Knight. } 7. Nxd4
{ Finally winning back the sacrificed pawn, increasing the pressure on  c6  . }
7... Bc5
{ Another counter-attack! Not the most popular move, but a solid move with the highest winrate for Black. }
