1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 { Scotch Game } 3... exd4
{ Trading a pair of center pawns. } 4. Nxd4 Bc5
{ Classical Variation, Attacking the Knight on  d4  with two minor pieces. } 5.
Nxc6 { Trading a pair of Knights. } 5... Qf6
{ Intermezzo Variation, An interesting zwischenzug, attacking the Knight with the Queen avoiding to ruin the pawn structure, while threatening checkmate on  f2  .   With  5...Qh4?  , Black doesn't achieve the same goal because of  6.Nd4  @@StartBracket@@+5.0@@EndBracket@@. }
6. Qf3 { Offering a trade of Queens. } 6... Qxc6 { Equalizing material. } 7.
Nc3 { A normal developing move, with a sneaky trap if Black isn't careful. }
7... d6
{ The fourth most popular move, hoping to bring out the Bishop on  c8  next move. But this is a huge blunder. }
8. Bb5
{ Oops! Skewering Queen and King! Black will lose his Queen @@StartBracket@@+7.5@@EndBracket@@. }
