{ The only move that gives White a small advantage. } 4... Nxf2
{ Black is hoping for  5.Kxf2?  Qh4+  , losing the Bishop next move @@StartBracket@@-3.5@@EndBracket@@. }
5. Qf3 { Threatening checkmate while attacking the Knight with the Queen. }
5... Qh4
{ Black's most challenging reply...   6.Qxf2  is bad in view of  6...Qxc4  @@StartBracket@@-2.0@@EndBracket@@. }
6. Qxf7+
{ Giving a check first. Notice that the Queen now is protecting the Bishop on  c4  . }
6... Kd8 7. Nf3
{ Developing the Knight, chasing away Black's Queen and preparing Bg5+, forking King and Queen. }
7... Nd3+ { Double check. The King has to move. } 8. Kd1
{ The safest square. Note that Black's Queen still is under attack. } 8... Nf2+
{ Check, forking King and Rook. } 9. Ke2
{ Ready to capture the Knight or to play Bg5+ next move @@StartBracket@@+8.0@@EndBracket@@. }
