{ This poor move was played over 10,000 times!! } 4. dxe5
{ The only move that gives White a small advantage. } 4... d5
{ Attacking the Bishop with a center pawn. One of the most common replies, but a very poor move... This position could also occur via:   @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/pppp1ppp/5n2/4p3/2B1P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQK1NR w KQkq - 2 3@@EndFEN@@  3.d4  d5  4.dxe5  Nxe4  . }
5. Bxd5
{ Taking with the Bishop generates more threats than taking with the Queen!   If you take with the Queen, probably a Queentrade will follow:  5.Qxd5  Qxd5  6.Bxd5  Nc5  @@StartBracket@@+1.5@@EndBracket@@. }
5... Nc5 { The most common reply. But this loses the game! } 6. Bxf7+
{ Sacrificing the Bishop on  f7  .   6...Kxf7  will be met by  7.Qxd8  @@StartBracket@@+9.0@@EndBracket@@. }
6... Ke7 { But this move is losing as well... } 7. Bg5+
{ Skewering King and Queen. The Queen will be lost next move, and Black can safely resign @@StartBracket@@+9.5@@EndBracket@@. }
