{ Berlin Defense, Attacking  e4  . } 3. d4
{ Ponziani Gambit, Attacking Black's center pawn. } 3... exd4 4. Nf3
{ Urusov Gambit, Sacrificing a pawn for quick development. } 4... Nxe4 5. Qxd4
{ Centralizing the Queen, attacking the Knight and the pawn on  g7  . } 5...
Nd6
{ Retreating the Knight, attacking White's Bishop on  c4  . Not a good move.   5...Nf6  would have been better. That way, White's Queen can't capture  g7  after the Bishop on  f8  leaves its spot @@StartBracket@@+0.0@@EndBracket@@. }
