{ The only move that gives White a big advantage! We have to bring the Rook into the game next. }
6... Nxc4
{ Capturing White's Bishop is a game-ending blunder...   6...Nc6  is bad too, in view of  7.Re1+  Ne7  8.Bb3  Ndf5  9.Qd5  , threatening checkmate on  f7  @@StartBracket@@+9.0@@EndBracket@@. }
7. Re1+
{ Check, exploiting the fact that Black's King isn't in a safe spot yet. } 7...
Be7 8. Qxg7 { Attacking the Rook in the corner. } 8... Rf8 9. Bh6
{ White now threatens checkmate on  f8  . The Bishop on  e7  is pinned to the King by the Rook @@StartBracket@@+12.5@@EndBracket@@. }
