{ Defending  f7  , challenging the Bishop on  c4  , but leaving  b7  unprotected. }
9. Qxb7 { Grabbing a free pawn! The Bishop is defended tactically. } 9... Bxc4
10. Qc6+ { Check, forking King and Bishop. } 10... Ke7 11. Qxc4
{ White has 2 pawns for his sacrificed piece, but Black has an ugly position. His King is in the center, and his pieces on the kingside have difficulties to get out @@StartBracket@@+0.5@@EndBracket@@. }
